From: canada-quant <pasta-paul@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: 2026-05-25
Subject: [PATCH] Marlin MoE: oversize workspace lock array 4x

The lock-array workspace in marlin_make_workspace_new() is sized at sms * max_blocks_per_sm
int32s. Under concurrent decode with moe_block_size==8, multiple blocks can transition slices
and bump locks_off past the allocation. With the JIT-PTX cubin (pre-PR #40923) this silently
read from caching-allocator slack; with the native sm_120a cubin (post #40923) it manifests as
cudaErrorIllegalAddress.

Companion to PR #36889 c_tmp fix. Together these resolve the 29/30 IMA we observe on RTX PRO
6000 (SM 12.0) with DeepSeek-V4-Flash W4A16+FP8+MTP under c=4 thinking-mode generation.

Symptom cross-references: #26558 (RTX 6000 Pro + GLM-4.6-GPTQ), #36811 (RTX A6000 + Qwen3.5-A3B),
#35922 (A100 + Qwen3-30B-A3B).

---
 vllm/model_executor/layers/quantization/utils/marlin_utils.py | 4 ++--
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/vllm/model_executor/layers/quantization/utils/marlin_utils.py b/vllm/model_executor/layers/quantization/utils/marlin_utils.py
--- a/vllm/model_executor/layers/quantization/utils/marlin_utils.py
+++ b/vllm/model_executor/layers/quantization/utils/marlin_utils.py
@@ -261,8 +261,8 @@ def marlin_make_workspace_new(
     device: torch.device, max_blocks_per_sm: int = 1
 ) -> torch.Tensor:
     sms = num_compute_units(device.index)
     return torch.zeros(
-        sms * max_blocks_per_sm, dtype=torch.int, device=device, requires_grad=False
+        sms * max_blocks_per_sm * 4, dtype=torch.int, device=device, requires_grad=False
     )
